  "text": "Combination and sequencing. The expressiveness of an MP approach can be significantly improved if multiple primitives can be simultaneously co-activated to compose more complex movements. However, most MP approaches do not support co-activation of primitives in a principled way. Instead, the concurrent activation requires a prioritization scheme [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] in order not to disrupt the motion. In our approach [CITATION_3] , we coactivate primitives to solve multiple tasks at the same time, without the need of such a scheme. Besides simultaneous activation, MP architectures aim to support sequencing MPs [CITATION_4] to acquire a smooth transition from one primitive to another. Such sequencing is needed to dynamically concatenate primitives in order to acquire longer, more complex movements. We show that in our framework a smooth transition can be achieved in a principled way similar to the combination of primitives.",
